,Recommended,227100,428393,"Posted: 1 April, 2013",all,｢C❤A｣ Pocahawtness,"This was so close to being a really good game! It’s scary, reasonably good graphics, and everything is as it should be.  However,  the shortage of ammo for close range guns, the slow rate of fire and reload,  means that this is about sitting as far away from the action as you can get and slowly picking the zombies off one by one. If they had changed the balance of the game a little, by including more ammo for the shotgun, and making reloads faster, and they would have brought players in closer to the action and dramatically improved the game.  As it stands, the pace is just too slow. The frequent slow-motion sequences really are unnecessary and really just make the game even slower. Recommended? If you plan on single player then I would say no, but the game does have some merit in four player coop, especially if you club together and buy the four game pack."
