76561198013594452,Not Recommended,227100,2852797,"Posted: 1 March, 2013",all,Firearm Encyclopedia,"This game has some good qualities and some bad qualities. First, the good; there's a lot of action, so that's pretty fun. There's some bullet drop for the sniper rifles, right on. The game rewards loot hunters, you'll find guns/ammo all over. The selection of firearms is quite good, something like 20 if I recall correctly. It's interesting being able to set up traps. The slow-mo hits are cool, it's a creepy and stressful game, as well as EXTREMILY difficult sometimes. I won't spoil anything but... that... friggin... church.I think that covers the good, now for the not so good; the MP40 fires too fast, SVT40 fires too slow, STG44 is too weak, M91/30's (Mosin Nagant) front sight is actually a Kar98k front sight, and the M1903's stock looks like a hybrid between a No.4 Lee Enfield and an M1917. From what I can tell, none of the scopes are accurate to real life. I find the special infected can be quite annoying, there is a serious lack of stealth for a sniper game, there is a serious lack of sniping for a sniper game (rarely go beyond 100m. Rarely go beyond 50m for that matter), one of my biggest gripes is there's no FPS option thus no aim down the sights option, and my last issue so far is I've been playing for roughly 2 hours now and it seems to be the same thing over and over:*SPOILERS* Fight a wave that instantly knows where you are. Fight another wave that instantly knows where you are. Fight another wave or two in the same manner. Find a safe house, restock on supplies, maybe change firearms. Fight a wave that instantly knows where you are. Fight a wave of jogging skeletons that instantly know where you are, fight a sniper who can jump better than spider man, fight another wave that instantly knows where you are. Safe house. Somewhere along the line is the friggin church. Maybe I'm just bad at 3rd person shooters, but I tried about a half dozen times to beat that friggin checkpoint with the MGing tank nazi, and I'm only on marksman (Normal).Draw your own conclusions. Want action? Perfect. Want realism with your shooting? Keep looking, or check out Red Orchestra."
