,Recommended,227100,9341685,"Posted: 4 March, 2014",all,Grapefruit,"Sniper Elite Nazi Zombie Army came out one year later than Sniper Elite V2. Its working on the same engine, even though graphic is quite different.The story is... below average, but, do you even need good a story to enjoy shooting nazi zombies?!  Anyway, story goes like this: The WW2 is almost over, allies are closing to the Berlin, but Hitler won't surrender that easily (of course). In his last attempt to save Germany he executes plan Z, that awakens the undead. That's the whole story pretty much.The gameplay is based on: killing zombies, surviving the zombie sieges, getting some relic, and getting to the safe room to rearm and start repeating the whole process. There is one boss, but you will battle him twice. There are couple type of the undead:1. zombies- they aren't too dangerous and are quite slow, but can (and probably will) revive if you don't shoot them in the head2. skeletons- quite fast, hitting quickly, they do quite of damage, but have low health3. suicide zombies- they just scream and run towards you with a grenade to blow you up (can be dangerous for whole team)4. gunner- does a LOT of damage with his machine gun and has a lot of healthAnd no, there isn't zombie Hitler.Bullet and xray killcam are here, but since this is rather fast game, when lots of enemies show up, you aren't gonna use your scope too much. The whole game has 6 levels and will last somewhere around 5-6 hours on regular difficulty.pros: different zombies to kill, fun with friends, pricecons: story, often repetition and predictabilitySo, I would recommend you this game if you plan to play it with friends. Otherwise, you might wanna hold with purchase."
