,Recommended,227100,9334639,"Posted: 3 March, 2014",all,Tears of Blood,"You'll notice a bad Metascore for this game. Don't always trust the Metascore. You know exactly what you are getting when you read the title of this game. You're going to be using a sniper rifle (primarily) to murder the living daylights out of nazi zombies. Now, I can understand if you just read that sentence and you said to yourself ""That sounds idiotic."" This game isn't for you, then. If you read that sentence, though, and you say to yourself ""That sounds fun as hell!"", then I can almost guarantee this game is worth your money, especially for how cheap it is.Let me get into the nitty-gritty here. The visuals for this game are superb. Some of the graphical options even kill my framerate, like supersampling. Not only are the textures fairly impressive, whether it be the evironment or the character models (i.e. the zombies), but the effects are pretty superb as well. In addition to that, the color scheme all-together visual style of the game is just amazing. You can look through my screenshots to see what I mean.The gamplay is exactly what you would expect, with an interesting flourish that relates back to the visuals. When you shoot a zombie with your sniper rifle, you have a certain likelihood that it will do an x-ray style kill-cam. Let me just say, that while it might get old after a while, it is very impressive to see. There are so many little details that you may not even notice at first. The bones will shatter in certain patters, lungs will deflate, eyes will pop out of sockets, blood will splatter and trail in the path the bullet takes after exiting, which will also twirl around, mangled and dented from impact. Did I mention the exploding heart, kidneys, and testicals? Now, I realize that's pretty violent, and obviously if this kind of thing makes you squeamish, but you still want to play, then you have the option to disable the kill-cam altogether. There are also some boss fights that are really fun as well. I'd say if this game had a weakness in the gameplay department, it would probably be that sometimes there are just -too many- zombies. They definitely go a little overboard, and some stages can drag, when you wish they would just end. I imagine most people will take breaks playing the game between stages because it really does fatigue you a bit.The music is pretty good, but not particularly memorable. Not much to say there. The zombies actually sound pretty scary when they are chanting or screaming or what have you. Probably the most appealing part of the sound design are the guns. They sound good, they sound powerful, just as they should.Now, where this game falls short...? The story. Were you expecting a story? You shouldn't be. I realize that we can get snobbish and start demanding good stories from everything under the sun these days, but really, I don't think it's necessary for every game that comes out. It has a plot, it's pretty weak, but it's not abhorrent considering the kind of game it is.Altogether, I really enjoy this game. It's great. I'll give it a solid 7/10. For me, that's a recommendation with an asterisk. Like I said, if you read the sentece from the beginning of this review, then you know exactly what you're getting, and if that's what you're looking for, then you're going to be pleased. If not, well then better to skip this and move on to something else."
