,Recommended,227100,7903444,"Posted: 3 December, 2013",all,Junaii,"This is an overlooked gem.I picked this up in a steam sale with no prior knowledge and I have to say it really impressed me. Firstly, I know this game was made for a relatively modest budget but the production values are up there with AAA titles. Graphics are very well done, animations, lighting and textures are impressive & it runs silky smooth. Its very solid with no noticable bugs and its obvious a lot of craft and care has gone into making this game as fun as possible.The premise is that its a (up to) four player, coop 3rd person shooter. As the title suggests the main antagonists are Nazi Zombies. The obvious comparisons to make are to Call of Duty: Black Ops coop nazi zombie mode and Left for Dead.While it borrows elements from each it does very much have its own ideas and its own character but if I was summarising it to a friend I would say its COD's zombies in Left for Dead style open levels.Levels are well designed and although quite linear they do give options for paths to take and for cover and at key points require teamwork and strategy from the coop players with enemies coming in multiple directions. The main weapon of choice is the sniper rifle and this adds an interesting game mechanic. Getting a headshot is immensly satisfying but when enemies start getting in close you can switch to a closer range weapon but ammo for these guns is in short supply. It really makes you think about each shot and makes things very tense when your in danger of getting overwhelmed.Sniper Elites party piece is there and is a gory and fun idea in a similar vein to Mortal Kombat's fatalities. When you get a certain kind of shot you get treated to a slow motion, xray view of the bullet passing through the body, causing horrendous damage to internal organs and bones. Even after a lot of play it can still be very satisfying to watch after a good shot.If you and some friends have played Left for Dead to death and want something new and a bit different and a hell of a lot of zombie blasting fun I recommend giving this a go. Im looking forward to grabbing to sequel soon as well"
