,Recommended,227100,8335584,"Posted: 27 December, 2013",all,Madame Écureuil,"When one thinks of zombie shooters, the kind of combat that usually comes to mind are close-quarters and brutal in nature which encourages twitch reactions and allows for some poor aiming. However, this game tried something new by taking the idea of methodical and deliberate long range combat prevalent in the Sniper Elite series with the legion of inexorable shambling Nazis.And the most amazing thing is, it actually works. The way that the weapons are balanced allows for a wide gamut of sniper rifles that are great for different situations, as well as a great selection of secondary weapons for when things get too intimate. From the PPSh-41 and it's extreme RoF, to the stopping power of the Trench gun, there is always a gun for every situation, and the challenge is executing your shots right.Being that this is a budget title made by Rebellion, I didn't expect this to be good and bought it for ironic entertainment value. Instead, I got genuinely entertained by the variety of weapons, and the zombies' reactions to being shot. Of course there are a LOT of rough edges to this game, like how hit detection for headshots can be spotty at times, or how the bullet vision can be annoying with how often it triggers.Do I recommend this game? Absolutely! Especially if you're looking for an alternative to Left 4 Dead 2, it is a blast on co-op."
