,Recommended,227100,14742043,"Posted: 5 March, 2015",all,Freyn.,"Whilst this is mostly Sniper Elite v2 with the undead in place of living enemies, to say that'sallit is would be really selling it short.The undead come in various shapes and sizes, mixed together to provide a different pace and challenge. More numerous than it's sequel but with a little less threat due to the map design I feel, it can still be quite overwhelming at times. Sadly as purely a campaign it can get repetitive and lacks that long term replayability (as do most similar games).What it really excels at is co-op play, and was clearly designed to be played on max difficulty with max players. Potentially a bit easier due to the ability to revive each other, don't let your guard down as you can quickly get overwhelmed by seemingly endless hordes. Sniper rifles versus slow moving targets may sound easy but they do a very good job of shuffling and swaying out of the way, providing some frustration at times.In single player the music combined with the blood-soaked, corpse ridden environment can get a bit creepy at times, but co-op turns it from more horror to action."
