,Not Recommended,227100,15120903,"Posted: 29 March, 2015",all,Setakat,"I would like to write a glowing review about this game, about how fun it is to kill Nazi Zombies. But I can't.Sniper Elite: Nazi Zombie Army sounds great when you say it out loud. It looks great written or typed.While Nazi Zombie Army sounds like a great idea to improve an already great game, it completely fails here. SE:NZA should be a great game, but sadly, it isn't.Everything that made Sniper Elite fun - is missing. There's no setup, no planning, no eliminating the odd patrolling enemy to get closer to your target, no setting up traps. Its just a 3rd person corridor shooter with a Sniper rifle, 10 mags of ammo, a SMG and 2 spare magazines, and your handgun and a dozen spare mags.I didn't get to do any real sniping apart from blowing away the odd half dozen Nazi Zombies while moving from horde fight to horde fight. And in those horder fights, I just used partial zoom to blow them away, used the SMG or Shotgun when they got too close, or rounded them into a circle and lobbed a grenade at them.For a series that revolves around sniping and stealth for its main selling points, NZA doesn't even bother trying to include them into its gameplay. Whats even worse is that I had more fun playing the various Call of Duty zombie survial modes.Going to leave this brain dead game to rot in a dark corner of my library, and go back to the true Sniper Elite roots."
