76561198005128610,Recommended,227100,21240180,"Posted: 15 February, 2016",all,the Winter Warlock,"This really was a fun game to play. So Ill vote YES for the most part. The other parts are just nuances Ill get into in a moment.So you are back in Berlin and it's a Zombie Army you are fighting. There are 5 maps to go through and I can say, this is a pretty EVIL game. Single player is pretty good and you can have up to 4 players in Multiplayer. Unfortunately when you play single player, you are alone. Unlike Left 4 Dead where you have 3 other AI's with you. This would have proved interesting for harder levels. But that's not the case. So that is one of my quirks. Once you get use to the gameplay, it's pretty straight forward. Zombies come at you and no use using stealth for the most parts. It's not going to work. They just come right for you. So keep your hearbeat down for any quick sprints you may need.The graphics are amazing! You are welcomed into the game with one of the most beautiful creeps scenes ever put on a game. Foggy everywhere and it's NIGHT time for this whole game. So I as usual, bought this on a discount and worth the $5. But one can easily be bored with single player, so let's head to multiplayer.Multiplayer is GREAT! Harder levels are easier with other live players. I breezed though the elite levels pretty fast. You have the options if you start a server on how many enemies you want 1-4x per person. That means 4 enemies per person if you choose 4x. But this can prove fatal becasue it seems servers are not really reliable and people lose the connection. They do eventually come back in, but sometimes the damage is done. AND I do see issues with delay. I find myself losing bullets fast when I shoot a good shot, but it doesn't register. Again, a few small issues.The music in the game is incredible. Sort of a 80's sound to it a little bit, but it is suiting to the game. Have a listen if you can.Hope you enjoy the gameUPDATE on multiplayer and lag.Well I believe it depends where you are player and where the server is. I have noticed that if I create the server, my lag is gone basically, and even other players don't have a problem."
,Not Recommended,227100,9370640,"Posted: 7 March, 2014",all,CorvusCorax,"Nazi Zombie Army is a fun game. You team up with 3 people and you start shooting Nazi zombie soldiers throughout the 5 chapters the game offers. As opposed to ""regular"" zombie games this one explains zombies by the good-old occultism background that gives the game a more creepy atmosphere: zombies have glowing eyes and the demonic laughter they occasionally produce can give everybody the creeps.Eliminating these otherworldly creatures with precision aiming is very exciting - wind is not taken into account as was in the original Sniper Elite games; this is as casual as it can get. Also, I liked how the developers tried to make this game authentic - objects and places feel realistic and you can really feel being part of an apocalyptic WW II era.And here comes the bad part: Finding players online is extremely difficult. I read many forums and I know there is a relatively big community and really wants to keep playing this game. I also had the chance of playing with 3 people several times only to find myself disconnected once a chapter ended. Some of these were friends on Steam and while chatting with them they confirmed having being disconnected. Playing the game alone is simply too difficult and boring - also, some achievements can only be attained in cooperative gameplay.If you want to play this game badly I suggest not only to wait for a big discount but also to gather at least 3 friends who want to desperately play it. With the 4 of you playing it together you can manage to have fun throughout but even with friends you'll experience disconnection several times.In addition to this the game also has a handful of bugs and glitches. I find it difficult to recommend a game that is marred by so many issues."
