,Recommended,227100,280553,"Posted: 13 July, 2013",all,Needs Food Badly,"-Large, pretty levels.-Nice '80's retro score.-The game's terrible cover mechanics and other tiny gameplay quirks reveal why most people hated the actual Sniper Elite game. However, they don't get much in the way here, since cover is rarely a thing you have to worry about (though there are some zombie snipers and gunner zombies; not many).-The game berating me for inevitably failing to put each of my bullets in the head of a zombie is amusing. ""Like a drunk who lost a bet!"" It's also nice to shoot a zombie's potato grenade and kill him and his nine best friends, even if that is almost always an accidental hit.-Don't play single player. It's completely boring and as soon as you start fighting skeletons (very early on) it is basically impossible. Four-player coop is more fun, and does require a little bit of teamwork. For the most part the game is a shooting gallery, but it does scratch an itch.-I see what people mean by the killcam being the highlight of this series. Unfortunately, it multiplayer it is sped up.Overall, worth the sale price of $5. It does get a little old after extended play time, but not too bad."
,Recommended,227100,11840469,"Posted: 23 August, 2014",all,Morning Wood,"This expansion alone far surpasses BO2 zombies and is on par with WaW and BO1 in terms of playability. It also has the added fear factor of using a sniper rifle, in close quarters, against hordes of the undead. Others may say the special infected such as snipers or gunners are the game's downfall, but I think it makes it more challenging, thus better. If you try to run inscreaming yolo, you will be torn to shreds. If you stand back and pick off the zombies one by one, you will burn through more ammo, yes, but you will be able to waltz right through the next checkpoint after. Ressurecting zombies are annoying, but they can be prevented from a headshot (even before they ressurect). Although the maps were taken right from the campaign, Rebellion reimagined them with the look of an apocalypse. The weapons provided are very balanced, so no player will have a huge advantage over another. X-ray kill cams even got a zombification, so if you wanna see zombie testicles explode, this is the game for you. 9/10"
