,Recommended,227100,1460157,"Posted: 2 March, 2013",all,J o n e x,"I have to admit, I wasn't impressed with Sniper Elite V2. It lacked a decent story and had limited gameplay. Sniper Elite: Nazi Zombie Army is what Sniper Elite V2 should have been. It’s just so much better killing hordes of zombies instead of a few sparse groups of Nazis. The same weapons are present (+ a few new ones I think), and the same equipment is available. Gameplay is identical to Sniper Elite V2 which fits in nicely to the survival genre. The enemies are more varied, some are suicidal, some are over-sized, some are extremely fast. There’s a good diversity to fight, and plenty of weapons to use (mostly rifles of course). The rifles don’t differ that much, some hit harder, some fire faster, but all of them kill zombies effectively. The bullet cam returns with it’s amazing x-ray kill shot  mode, this time with a decaying zombie corpse!There’s a single player campaign which is fun to play, but the co-op campaign is where you get your real money’s worth. Enemy density is determined by how many players are in the match, so 2 players means a challenge, and 4 players means prepare for a massacre :P It really is fun to battle the zombie apocalypse alongside friends. The levels are linear, but quite large to allow different options and vantage points for all players. With only 5 missions, the campaign won’t last long, but Sniper Elite difficulty will have you coming back if you’re thirsty for a challenge.A great standalone game that was worth the pre-order, and something that I‘ll be playing with friends until that ♥♥♥♥♥y elite difficulty has been beaten."
