,Recommended,227100,9863465,"Posted: 18 April, 2014",all,The Ancient Wizard,"Since Sniper Elite: Nazi Zombie Army and its sequel are essentially the same game I feel that one review is necessary.The concept of Nazi Zombies isn’t anything new. However to have a campaign based completely around a zombified Deutschland did arouse my curiosity. To say I was astonished is a bit much, and to say I was disgruntled isn’t necessary either. There are pros and cons to this game.The Good.The series features a foggy, bloodied Germany. Something that really isn’t new in any zombie-based video game. However the rules of double tap, beware of bathrooms and the buddy system are all legible in this game. After striking down a kill if it wasn’t a headshot, it’ll probably resurrect. Beware of anywhere really; zombies either dig themselves out of the ground or were sleeping where they died in their previous life. The buddy system is the most important during cooperative play. Due to the explosive zombies or the rifle wielding ones you will get downed a lot. Something that most zombie games don’t have is slow lumbering zombies and that is what this game has. I appreciate the classic zombie speed, giving there is large quantities of zombies to balance it. Oh and the x-ray vision of a zombie’s skull being pierced is the most thrilling thing ever!The Bad.The series is a mixture of Left 4 Dead and Call of Duty’s Nazi Zombies. First thing first is Survive the Siege, where a large group of zombies know where you are at. Which isn’t bad, but when your game is 50% siege survival it does get a little dull. The next thing is Get to the Safehouse which for some reason every safehouse in every zombie game is stockpiled with weapons, ammo, enough trip mines to destroy the fatherland then how is it there are only four survivors?How do these guys even know where the safehouse is? I know there is two playable german characters but in all the destruction you can recognize where the safe houses are? Another problem is the other generic thing: Zombie Subclasses, can someone tell me why there are zombies that know how to use guns and others that don’t? What about the annoying “Kamikaze” zombies? At least zombies with guns lumber these zombies just sprint at you full force and usually a single bullet doesn’t stop them. The thing that makes me laugh is the demon circles summoning the Spooky Scary Skeletons. The final thing that is bland is the boss battles. Why is every boss battle a Nazi ghost that summons nazi zombies? Sure the one at the cathedral was okay. But why is there more than that? Surely you could have incorporated Zombie Hitler instead of just killing him off.The Ugly.Game has more graphic bugs than anything. When turning on Cinema grain effect some zombies have glowing heads. Random textures and bump mapping data screw up as soon as you mess with the graphics in-game. Then there is the broken servers where you just cleared the siege and the next mission starts except for the fact the invisible walls didn’t disappear and everyone is waiting for the mission that never comes. But my biggest pet peeve is broken collision meshes. I strike a zombie twice in the head both bullets failed to make contact. Sometimes the clipping floor panels trap you until Mr.Full-Metal-Jack shoots you dead. Another pet peeve is why do some bullet pierce the body but make no wounds?OVERALL--Graphics : 6/10Gameplay : 8/10Story : 3/10Multiplayer : 5/10Final Outlook: Game that is action-packed with everyone’s zombie killing needs, if you want a fun game with little to no storyline this is perfect for you."
