,Recommended,227100,1845215,"Posted: 1 October, 2013",all,YoGattoGatto,"Feels shallow so far, not much to say about it.  If you really like the Sniper Elite series, it is a decent addition, but there are some significant issues.I have played with both a mouse and KB, as well as an Xbox controller, and I find the controlls when aiming to be top notch, but while moving....Ok, so the guy runs, but if I am not facing an item directly, he will not pick it up. If I am not facing it correctly, it won't bring up the interaction button for opening doors or searching enemies.  Again, if you are not DIRECTLY facing the specific part of a wall that allows a vault, he will not vault.  THIS IS CRUCIAL!!!Why is this so annoying do you ask?  Let me digress a bit...In past Sniper games, there is much SNEAKING and PLANNING.In THIS Sniper game, there is much running, and alot less planning.  The zombies come at you in hoards, often with the section you are in being blockaded so you are limited on where you can front an attack.  This does not work well with zombies that do not try to hide, they just keep following you.So while you are busy trying to find a good spot to shoot from, you are constantly having to pop a couple and GO!  You cannot stand still for long.I was expecting more room for strategy, and so far the game is kind of boring me.  Not too much story yet, and like I said, strategy is not really given time to happen.If you enjoy the bullet time of Sniper Elite, it is fun to watch zombies get ripped apart.But if you like the sneaking and SNIPER feel to the gameplay, do not expect it so much here.Pick it up on sale, but remember that it is gonna feel like an arcade game, rather than a good Sniper experience."
