,Not Recommended,227100,10891329,"Posted: 27 June, 2014",all,id10m,"No. Just, no.Imagine you took a reasonably good game about sniping -- i.e., sneaking around, finding vantage points, staying undetected,  monitoring and avoiding patrolling guards, and finally accounting for distance, wind and other factors to take out high-value targets with one well-placed rifle shot through the eye from as far away as possible -- imagine you took a game like that and systematically removed everything that was good about it.Sneaking is useless because apparently enemies can smell you even through walls, and they'll spawn out of the ground on top of you or as soon as you cross some invisible ""time for more zombies"" line. Finding vantage points is worthless because if you can see the enemy, they've already spawned at close range and are shambling toward you, and if you can't see the enemy, it's because they haven't magically spawned yet. You can look all day and you won't see them until you cross that invisible line to spawn them. Monitoring enemy movements is useless; they're either aware and coming right for you, or they don't exist yet. And actual opportunities to actually play as an elite sniper are few and far between. You're much better off ditching the Garand and sticking to shotguns and machine guns.Why would anyone do this to a sniper game? You'd have to be some kind of brain-dead Nazi."
