76561198247365794,Not Recommended,227100,19137654,"Posted: 17 November, 2015",all,nilesthrompton,"In what appears to be par for the Sniper Elite series, Nazi Zombie Army suffers from a notable lack of imagination.  Departing from even the regular series stream (which I actually prefer, and which I have enjoyed, as the 'sniper' designation fits those games very well), this is an almost entirely 'shoot em up' based game, which appears to ditch the sniper aspect of the series, referring you instead to level after level of 'survive this horde by blasting them away'.  There's such a serious lack of strategy here, that - after logging in about 5 hours total - I don't think I've been able to play through an entire round (of killing endless mobs of nearly identical enemies), without becoming strikingly bored and disinterested.  Much like the Dead Island series fell flat, and brought its share of disrepute to the zombie/undead game genre, this is a similarly forgettable addition to the zombie gaming series.  For future developers - the golden rule of content in gaming is; if you have nothing unique to add to a genre beyond a mildly entertaining shoot-em-up action game, then you'd best leave it to the developers who have real experience and expertise in the genre, instead of wading into an unfamiliar genre with mixed results at best.  Final verdict - this game is at the level of a free DLC, and little more."
