76561197966440985,Recommended,227100,243285,"Posted: 16 July, 2013",all,Fuzero,"THIS GAME IS ♥♥♥♥IN"" AWESOME!!! Seriously though; it seemlessly flips between an 80's synth soundtrack that screams ""Kurt Russel Action Film!"" and some of the best horror music and sound effects I've come across in a game. The weapons feel accurate to their real-world counter-parts (I've fired a few of these, not all) and the sniping action is tactile and addicting. The 4-player co-op will keep you playing till you get ""single-man's arm"" provided you get a good connection (about 50% of the time time it's perfect, and 50% of the time is tolerable but never bad). The level design feels like a linear corridor at first, but you'll quickly realize that there are windows to leap through, choke points for booby traps, hallways for ""funnels of death"" and open areas for killing fields. I paid $5 for it during the summer sale, and it was worth every penny. Possibly the best $5 I've spent in a long time; if the price were higher I would still recommend it!"
