76561198082915043,Recommended,227100,7832830,"Posted: 29 November, 2013",all,gameintruder💋,"This game is great.  I love the beautiful graphics.  But best of all, the gameplay is excellent.  This game offers a challenging, and intense adventure while trying to survive the never ending horde of Nazi zombies everywhere.  This game is best played with friends in coop mode, although playing in single player mode is much more fun.EDIT:  March 19, 2014After trying out this game with a few of my friends I can honestly say, STAY AWAY FROM IT!  Everything is great until you start to play Cooperative Mode.  Laggy as hell, you get dropped by the game so many times, it just becomes outright frustrating.  The other Major problem is communication between players.  There is no OPTION in the game to make it OPEN MIC and so the Push To Talk becomes tedious and very upsetting.  We have never been able to finish the game because of one glitchy problem after the next.  You shoot a zombie, and u feel like your shooting blanks.  the shots won't register for about 2 full seconds.  A delay that none of us care for.  And people have left the game because it's just too much trouble.  There's no real checkpoint where u can start over again without ending up in the beginning of the level again.  and there are no options for this either.  What is sad is that this game could've been perfect if there were updates to fix these so called glitches.  Yet, they still exist.  If there is no support for this game, i think STEAM should STOP selling it.  Nobody wants to pay for an UNSUPPORTED GLITCHY game that later u will just want to bury it deep in it's own grave along with the glitchy zombies.  What a disappointment.  Buyer Beware!EDIT: July 21, 2017since my last review on March 19, 2014, the game has had many patches and updates and is now working perfectly. you still need skype to communicate, but it's a minor inconvenience to me now. i updated my graphics card and it seemed to fixed the many problems that upset me (the previous card was not being supported any longer by Nvidia). in short, this is a very entertaining game, and i definitely recommend it now that it's fixed."
